  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/breaking_news/\u0d86\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dae\u0dd2\u0d9a-\u0d9c\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dc5\u0dd4-\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0db3\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7-\u0d85\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4-\u0d85\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca-\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2-\u0d85\u0dc0\u0db0\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca/11-396608",
  "time_ut": 1661422356,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d86\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dae\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dc5\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0db3\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0d85\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0d85\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0db0\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "More attention in interim budget to solve economic problems",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister-in-Charge Mr. Prasanna Ranatunga has instructed the officials to pay more attention to solving the economic problems facing the country in the proposed interim budget and to pay more attention to it while preparing the proposals of the Ministry of Urban Development and Housing.",
        "Accordingly, the minister expressed confidence that as soon as the economic condition of the country improves, all the currently stopped projects will be able to be started promptly.",
        "The minister mentioned this in a discussion held yesterday (24th) with the ministry officials at the ministry auditorium in Setsiripaye, Battaramulla regarding the preparation of interim budget proposals.",
        "The President said that the government expects to give more priority through the new budget to increase the tourism business next year. While preparing the budget proposals, attention should be paid to it and a related plan should be formed at the district level. It would be good if programs like 'Mihidu Nivahana', which are good for the country, were continued without stopping. But because the economic condition of the country was not good, we had to stop many projects. But as soon as the economic situation improves, all the projects that have been stopped will be restarted quickly.",
        "Therefore, all the ministry officials should come together and prepare a common proposal by receiving budget proposals at the institution level. The minister also mentioned that more attention should be given to areas such as encouraging foreign direct investments favorable to the country, reviving tourism and small scale businesses, reforming state businesses by merging institutions, and ensuring food security in the country.",
        "Urban Development and Housing Ministry Secretary Pradeep Ratnayake, Additional Secretary (Housing and Construction) Keerthi Ranjith Abeysiriwardena, Additional Secretary (Coastal Conservation and Lowlands) Anil Wijesiri, Additional Secretary (Estate Housing) D.D. Mr. Matararachchi and a group of officials including chief financial officers, directors and accountants of the ministry participated in this event."
      ],
